## Introduction
The data schema (also known as **Contract **or **Contract file**) is an XML file containing the definitions of datasections and attributes used for the issue of documents piloted by the variable data.

### Example XML contract file
`&lt;?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?&gt;
        &lt;contract&gt;
        &lt;datasection name="FILE" repeatable="false"&gt;
        &lt;datasection name="DOCUMENT" repeatable="true"&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="date" type="string" length="50"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="code" type="string" length="100"/&gt;
        &lt;datasection name="PROFILE" repeatable="false"&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="customerCode" type="string" length="20"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="firstName" type="string" length="100"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="middleName" type="string" length="100"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="lastName" type="string" length="100"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="fullName" type="string" length="210"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="fullNameAddress" type="string" length="303"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="addressLine1" type="string" length="100"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="addressLine2" type="string" length="100"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="addressCity" type="string" length="100"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="addressZipCode" type="string" length="100"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="addressStateShort" type="string" length="100"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="addressStateLong" type="string" length="100"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="customerType" type="string" length="50"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="profileType" type="string" length="50"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="email" type="string" length="250"/&gt;
        &lt;datasection name="BRANCH" repeatable="false"&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="bic" type="string" length="30"/&gt;
        &lt;attribute name="bankName" type="string" length="75"/&gt;
        ....`The data schema consists of a hierarchical structure of datasections, within which the attributes to be used for management of the variable data within each document can be selected.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Speech**

Speech attribute. To use Text-To-Speech in a Pvideo, a specific attribute of type Speech must be added in the Contract Data File.

> Warning

This attribute cannot be used in a rule set or in variable data

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Repeatable**

Indicates that the content is repeatable.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Shipment selector**

Indicates that the datasection is set as a shipment selector.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Document selector**

Indicates that the datasection is set as a document selector.

## Finding a datasection or an attribute
The displayed list can be searched using keywords.

## Quick search
Do one of the following operations to perform a quick search.

- Enter the text to be used as a search parameter. 

- Click on the search icon.

- Jump between search results using the arrows icons.

-  Retrieve attribute usage statistics clicking on the corresponding button.

## Retrieving usage statistics
Clicking on the Retrieve usage statistics button, Document Composition will count attributes that are in use with a different color from those who aren't, as made evident by the following picture.

## Exporting usage statistics
Inside the data schema is possible to copy the calculated statistics into a clipboard by clicking on the ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon.

The output file will be in a tab-delimited file with double quotes as qualifier, in order to view them in a worksheet, as shown in the example below.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The selector management panel at the bottom of the screen can be used to select a datasection from the data schema for selection of a shipment or a document during print spool generation.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Setting a shipment selector
Select the name of the datasection that you wish to use as shipment selector using the **Shipment Selector menu**. The symbol	![](data:image/png;base64,) will be displayed next to the name of the datasection.

### Setting a document selector
Select the name of the datasection that you wish to use as document selector using the **Document Selector menu**. The symbol ![](data:image/png;base64,) will be displayed next to the name of the datasection.

### Setting a shipment identifier attribute
Select the name of the attribute that you wish to use as Shipment selector (optional, used in Pvideo).
